ISLAMABAD, Aug 24 (APP):South Asia Bureau Chief of BBC News Jacky Martens called on Caretaker Prime Minister Anwaar-ul-Haq Kakar here on Thursday and discussed matters of mutual interest.
She briefed the prime minister about expansion of BBC presence in Pakistan. Federal Ministers for Information and Broadcasting Murtaza Solangi and Minister for Interior Sarfraz Bugti were also present.
